<br>
Second: What did we learn to be better for next time?<br>
<br>
Some observations on my part...<br>
<br>
1) Tanks don't do much except bang on doors. But... If I finish out my crafting skills, then we could have 2 or more catapults on the doors. We might actually just want to have Nimitz or some other friendly crafter make a couple and release them to lower folks or semi-useless tanks. Coordinating catapult fire could make a rather large dent in the attackers. A few tanks will need to take care of the pets that somehow sneak underneath the doors. If enough time passes, someone will have to repair the cats and maybe feed ammunition if in a merchant keep.<br>
<br>
2) Upgrade the keep guards right before we know an assault is coming. (I think this was mentioned by Bels. I'm stealing with pride!)<br>
<br>
3) Except for stealthers, stay inside the gates. Armsmen who fall off walls die really quick and cannot be rez'ed.<br>
<br>
4) Decide who will be MA before every fight or when groups change. No, you won't win, but you will take a few more RP's with you. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
5) What have I missed? Please feel free to add to our knowledge base. Each time we do this we will get a little better. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Cheers, <p>Niz, Tavik, etc...<BR>
Forgotten Truth</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/udunkar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dunkar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(5/4/02 5:19:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1110.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Keep defense</span><hr size=1> For defending a keep, here are a few things I have learned in my outings that seem to help.<br>
<br>
1)  If you are a caster/archer type, never stay in an open window too long.  Once you appear you will be targeted by the enemy.  Most people can take one, maybe two shots before dieing.  If you stay too long you are painting a neon &quot;hit me&quot; tag on you.<br>
<br>
2)  Become familier with the climb in points and how to defend them.  Never expose your front or back to them, unless you have the stealther targeted and starting to attack.  This is harder for the non-assassins since your detection radius is smaller.  For the higher lvl tanks/melee classes defending a climb point, stay in combat mode.  As soon as you are hit, you swing back.  After a few of these the climber will start looking for other climb points.<br>
<br>
3)  Some of the best fights in a keep defense are in the lord room.  When it looks like the last door will fall, head up and be ready to AE, stun, mez, throw the kitchen sink...  With the small area, a good AE nuke will do max damage.  During the beno siege this week, the mids killed 15 people in a matter of 5 seconds with their AE stun/nukes.  That alone turned the tides to thier favor.<br>
<br>
For the use of siege weapons, I think we should have a little get together at one of the bandit camps one night.  Bring supplies to make a few of the different siege items and take turns getting used to how they work, targeting, loading and firing.  Thoughts???<br>
<br>
Dunkar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/urajivan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rajivan</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(5/4/02 9:24:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1110.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Keep defense</span><hr size=1> I learned alot from watching while dead at the gate keeper last night too.  Their forces weren't much bigger if at all than ours were when we took the keep.  I think we could have done alot more damage if we were already outside the keep (maybe hiding behind it) and then ambush them from the sides and rear as they are concentrating on the doors.  Especially after the guards spawned on them for a second time.  <br>
<br>
Aroqua was able to take a few out from behind the scene and that really gets them out of control.  I think to win you must do things that are not expected.  <br>
<br>
Another suggestion, park our Infiltrators on the ground near the walls and/or corners and identify the climbers on their way up.  Then let the casters nuke away at them from below <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway, just my 2 cents worth.  I had a blast and hope we can do this on a regular basis.<br>
<br>
Raj <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ucreepypete.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CreepyPete</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(5/4/02 11:38:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1110.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Keep defense</span><hr size=1> The way keeps are currently implemented they are, in many cases, a liability to the defenders. Almost impossible to shoot out of and it's a lot easier to shoot in than out. Hell, if keeps were like this in RL no one would even have built em except to keep the rain off. Really Mythic needs to address the crappy LOS issues for keep defense to be anything more than random AEs and holing up in the lord room. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uaroqua.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aroqua</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(5/6/02 11:40:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1110.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Defending</span><hr size=1> WEll, I basically was scouting down the road when i saw the force incoming to Bled. So I warned in group that they werew on the way. From there I stealthed back up to Bled and made use of the rear of the army since they didn't place a rear guard. I waited for the Mids to come down and heal, then fired away. Most of these turned out to be 1 shot kills that allowed me to run away, atealth, and switch to other side of road to mark my next target. It did seem to disrupt them a bit until they got into the keep.<br>
